CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 31, 1953, pg. 27, reads: "Fifth, Westinghouse in Hot Fight for Cage Title - Fifth Avenue Cagers - Fifth Avenue, which is staging a dogged fight for supremacy in Section One of the City League basketball race has one of the best teams the school has floored in several years. Pictured above are, left to right, back row, George Cupples, head coach; Melvin Brown, Donald Feabry, John Washington and Joe Statts [Stotts]. Front row: George Brown, Ralph McNeal and Jewell Ledbetter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Fifth Avenue High School basketball team, kneeling from left: George "Due" Brown, captain Ralph "Bunky" McNeal, Jewel or Jewell Ledbetter; standing: coach George Cupples, Melvin Brown, Donald "Don" Feabry, John Washington, and Joe Stotts, posed in gymnasium
